    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Post WWII, Eastman Kodak introduced verifax copiers intended as an office reprographic tool. The process produced poor quality reproductions that were prone to fading, and required special paper.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051904/Smithsonian Studies in History and Technology (2010-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Na de Tweede Wereldoorlog introduceerde Eastman Kodak de Verifax-kopieermachine, die was bedoeld als reprografisch hulpmiddel op kantoor. Het procedé resulteerde in reproducties van slechte kwaliteit, die gevoelig waren voor vervaging en die speciaal papier vereisten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>二戰後，伊士曼‧柯達(Eastman Kodak)意圖推行照相沖印印表機做為辦公室的複印設備。這種機器的產品品質低劣，易於褪色，並且需要使用特殊的紙張進行複印。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
